<div class="prose">

  <h1>
    Installing Unpoly
  </h1>


  <h2>Requirements</h2>

  <p>
    Unpoly's single dependency is <a href="https://jquery.com/">jQuery</a> 1.9 or higher.
  </p>

  <p>
    Unpoly works with almost all applications that render HTML on the server.
    You can write your server-side code in any programming language (Ruby, PHP, Node.js, Java, Elixir â€¦).
  </p>

  <h2>Library files</h2>

  <p>
    Unpoly consists of both JavaScript and (minimal) CSS files:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <code>unpoly.min.js</code> (<%= unpoly_library_size('unpoly.min.js') %>)
    </li>
    <li>
      <code>unpoly.min.css</code> (<%= unpoly_library_size('unpoly.min.css') %>)
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    There are some <b>optional</b> files will help you if you are using <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/">Bootstrap</a>:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <code>unpoly-bootstrap3.min.js</code> (<%= unpoly_library_size('unpoly-bootstrap3.min.js') %>)
    </li>
    <li>
      <code>unpoly-bootstrap3.min.css</code> (<%= unpoly_library_size('unpoly-bootstrap3.min.css') %>)
    </li>
  </ol>


  <h2>Installation methods</h2>

  <p>
    You have multiple options for downloading and integrating Unpoly:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="#cdn">Link to a CDN</a> (easiest if you want to test-drive)</li>
    <li><a href="#npm">Install with npm</a></li>
    <li><a href="#rails">Install with Ruby on Rails</a></li>
    <li><a href="#bower">Install with Bower</a></li>
    <li><a href="#zip">Download as ZIP</a></li>
    <li><a href="#git">Clone with Git</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="rails">Install with Ruby on Rails</h2>

  <p>
    Unpoly is available as a Ruby gem that makes the library's JavaScript and CSS sources
    available to the Rails asset pipeline. It also includes
    <a href="http://www.rubydoc.info/github/unpoly/unpoly/master">some useful helpers</a>
    for your controllers and views.
  </p>

  <p>
    To install Unpoly in Rails, add the following line to your <code>Gemfile</code>:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="ruby">gem 'unpoly-rails'</code></pre>

  <p>Now run <code>bundle install</code> and restart your development server.</p>

  <p>Add the following line to your <code>application.js</code> manifest:</p>

  <pre><code class="javascript">//= require unpoly</code></pre>

  <p>
    Also add the following line to your <code>application.css</code> manifest:</p>
  </p>

  <pre><code class="css">/*
 *= require unpoly
 */</code></pre>

  <h3>Installing with Bootstrap integration</h3>

  <p>If you want to use Unpoly's Bootstrap integration, add the following to your <code>application.js</code> manifest <b>after requiring Bootstrap</b>:</p>

  <pre><code class="javascript">//= require unpoly
//= require unpoly-bootstrap3</code></pre>

  <p>
    Also add the following to your <code>application.css</code> manifest <b>after requiring Bootstrap</b>:</p>
  </p>

  <pre><code class="css">/*
 *= require unpoly
 *= require unpoly-bootstrap3
 */</code></pre>


  <h2 id="npm">Install with npm</h2>

  <p>
    Install the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/unpoly">npm package</a>:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="nohighlight">npm install unpoly</code></pre>

  <p>
    This will download the files to
    <code>node_modules/unpoly/dist</code>.
  </p>


  <h2 id="bower">Install with Bower</h2>

  <p>
    Install the <a href="http://bower.io/">Bower</a> package:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="nohighlight">bower install unpoly</code></pre>

  <p>
    This will download the files to
    <code>bower_components/unpoly/dist</code>.
  </p>


  <h2 id="cdn">Link to a CDN</h2>

  <p>
    You can link to the Unpoly files directly from a CDN:
  </p>

  <%= partial 'install/cdn_tags' %>

  <h4>Linking with Bootstrap integration</h4>

  <p>If you want to use Unpoly's Bootstrap integration, link to the following URLs instead:</p>

  <%= partial 'install/cdn_bootstrap_tags' %>

  <p>
    Note that you need to trust the CDN.
  </p>

  <h2 id="zip">Download as ZIP</h2>

  Download the <a href="https://github.com/unpoly/unpoly/archive/v<%= guide.version %>.zip">minified files and complete source code</a>:

  <pre><code class="nohighlight">curl -LO https://github.com/unpoly/unpoly/archive/v<%= guide.version %>.zip
unzip v<%= guide.version %>.zip</code></pre>

  <p>
    After unzipping the minified files will be in the <code>unpoly-<%= guide.version %>/dist</code> directory.
  </p>

  <h2 id="git">Clone with Git</h2>

  <p>
    Clone the project from <a href="https://github.com/unpoly/unpoly">GitHub</a>
    and checkout the release:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="nohighlight">git clone https://github.com/unpoly/unpoly.git
cd unpoly
git checkout v<%= guide.version %></code></pre>

</div>

